)	At the hearing, the Commission submitted that the purpose of requiring the customs authorities to provide information was simply to identify which exporting producers were affected. This made it possible to review the documentation submitted by each exporting producer in their original MET and IT claims and avoided the delays associated with considering cases in which no applications for refunds had been made.

